vectorData.altText: 7. Which spinal levels contribute to the formation of the medial cord of the brachial plexus (as indicated by the arrow)?
That's right!  The medial cord of the brachial plexus contains fibres from the C8 - T1 levels.

Each of the three trunks bifurcate, and the divisions thus formed join to create the lateral, medial and posterior cords of the brachial plexus. 
The cords of the brachial plexus are named according to their position relative to the axillary artery.
